<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Letter</div>
<div class="nbunit" id="17Mar1933"><font color="red">17 March 1933</font> <i>Letters III</i> (to Harriet Weaver from Paul L&eacute;on): Hull Daily Mail [copies] &hellip; What [Mr Joyce] needs principally is I firmly believe some absolute rest and this he is not only not getting now but seems to despair of getting ever &hellip; The visit to Zurich is necessary &hellip; About Mr Budgen &mdash; for completion of his book he must go to Dublin in order to paint Chapel Izod (I am not sure of my spelling) the source of the Liffey to illustrate his book </div>
